				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{Directionality}=\frac{\mathrm{d}}{\mathrm{D}} $$\end{document}Directionality=dDwhere d represents the distance between the starting and ending points of the target cell and D represents the total length of the trajectory of the target cell. Confocal and live cell imaging data were acquired at the Brain Research Core Facilities in KBRI (Korea).
